SIMPLE: faithful
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Faithful
<hw>Faith"ful</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Full of
faith, or having faith; disposed to believe, especially in the
declarations and promises of God.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>You are not <qex>faithful</qex>, sir.</q> <rj><qau>B.
Jonson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Firm in adherence to promises, oaths, contracts,
treaties, or other engagements.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>faithful</qex> God, which keepeth covenant and mercy with
them that love him.</q> <rj><qau>Deut. vii. 9.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>True and constant in affection or allegiance to a
person to whom one is bound by a vow, by ties of love, gratitude, or
honor, as to a husband, a prince, a friend; firm in the observance of
duty; loyal; of true fidelity; <as>as, a <ex>faithful</ex> husband or
servant</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>So spake the seraph Abdiel, <qex>faithful</qex> found,⟦br⟧
Among the faithless, <qex>faithful</qex> only he.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Worthy of confidence and belief; conformable to
truth ot fact; exact; accurate; <as>as, a <ex>faithful</ex> narrative or
representation</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>It is a <qex>faithful</qex> saying.</q> <rj><qau>2 Tim. ii.
11.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>The Faithful</b></col>, <cd>the adherents of any system
of religious belief; esp. used as an epithet of the followers of
Mohammed.</cd></cs></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Trusty; honest; upright; sincere; veracious;
trustworthy.</syn></p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Faith"ful*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos>
-<wf>Faith"ful*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>faithfulness</ent>⟦br⟧
